    },
    {
      "id": "19d0d72302e4758aa2b6b70f3eb2e093c8dfcb2d",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2012-05-22 17:31:26.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\n(7 inline comments)\n\nPatch itself looks reasonable, though I'm not an expert in the lu_context code.  My main objection relates to commenting out the lu_device_type_fini() code and hoping that some later patch will restore this functionality.\n\nOne way to handle this is to submit a follow-on patch to this one that re-enables lu_device_type_fini() that can be landed once LU-1417 is on master (possibly immediately after this one), so that at least it is tracked in Gerrit instead of just being a comment in the code.  In this third case, I will change my inspection of this patch to +1 when the follow-on patch appears.\n\nAlternately, if LU-1417 lands before this patch (which is likely, due to the many dependencies this patch has), this patch can rebased and remove the commented-out code at that time.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "2b733687322f5bf43abd7f31f1d0414959d8a1db",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 176,
        "name": "Liang Zhen",
        "email": "liang.zhen@intel.com",
        "username": "liangzhen",
