    {
      "id": "3b04d7155b3cf7c51897f7e5932c0ba2378a0967",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 176,
        "name": "Liang Zhen",
        "email": "liang.zhen@intel.com",
        "username": "liangzhen",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2012-06-08 04:25:03.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nI will investigate whether we need set \"REMEMBER\" flag for ptlrpc_request::rq_session, but please look into lu_context_fini()->keys_fini(), it must lock lu_key_guard (I remember there will be a problem if we don't), and it's a somehow expensive operation, so I think we still need this improvement right?\n\nI remember long time ago, I got lockmeter stats and it shows that keys_fini() got really high lock contention.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "763566663845066d45e926528fc303fd175783d8",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 4,
